pullRequest.body:
Add the fixed point theorem for (omega) complete partial orders and Kleene's fixed point theorem for complete lattices.

---
Some comments regarding this PR:
- ~~I decided to use the function `Nat.repeat` as the approximation scheme. There are good reasons to do this and good reasons to use a function defined yourself. Since the lemmas `Nat.repeat_le` and `Nat.monotone_repeat` can be useful outside this theorem and the interpretation as a chain `repeatChain` was added anyway, I decided against an approximation definition, unlike how the fixed point theorems in `Mathlib.Control` do it.~~ I switched to `Nat.iterate`
- You could argue which version exactly is Kleene's fixed point theorem --- the one on omega complete partial order or on complete lattices. I have seen both. Since the source in omega complete partial order does not call it this way, I decided to call the complete lattice variant like this. But I have no strong feeling which to call Kleene's fixed point theorem.

I welcome any feedback and happy to incorporate them!

[![Open in Gitpod](https://gitpod.io/button/open-in-gitpod.svg)](https://gitpod.io/from-referrer/)

nodes.body: Note that Mathlib mostly uses `Nat.iterate` instead of `Nat.repeat` (and has a file about `Monotone` and `Nat.iterate`). We should resolve this issue some day, but I think that it's better to stick to `iterate` for now.

I was already very irritated about the lack of proofs of `Nat.repeat`... The switch to `Nat.iterate` was surprising difficult (as `Nat.iterate` unfolds inwards) but it should be replaced everywhere.

Also, a documentation string on `Nat.repeat` to use `Nat.iterate` instead could be added in the short term.

```suggestion
open OmegaCompletePartialOrder fixedPoints

/-- **Kleenes fixed point Theorem**: The least fixed point in a complete lattice is
the supremum of iterating a function on bottom arbitrary often. -/
theorem lfp_eq_sSup_repeat (h : Continuous f) :
    lfp f = sSup { Nat.repeat f n ⊥ | n : Nat} := by
  apply le_antisymm
  · apply lfp_le_fixed
    exact Function.mem_fixedPoints.mp (ωSup_repeat_mem_fixedPoint ⟨f, h⟩ ⊥ bot_le)
  · apply le_lfp
    intro a h_a
    exact ωSup_repeat_le_prefixedPoint ⟨f, h⟩ ⊥ bot_le h_a bot_le

theorem gfp_eq_sSup_repeat (h : Continuous (OrderHom.dual f)) :
    gfp f = sInf { Nat.repeat f n ⊤ | n : Nat} :=
  lfp_eq_sSup_repeat (OrderHom.dual f) h
```

nodes.body: Note that Mathlib mostly uses `Nat.iterate` instead of `Nat.repeat` (and has a file about `Monotone` and `Nat.iterate`). We should resolve this issue some day, but I think that it's better to stick to `iterate` for now.

I was already very irritated about the lack of proofs of `Nat.repeat`... The switch to `Nat.iterate` was surprising difficult (as `Nat.iterate` unfolds inwards) but it should be replaced everywhere.

Also, a documentation string on `Nat.repeat` to use `Nat.iterate` instead could be added in the short term.
